        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Brook Street</placeName>
                    <date>May 19</date>
                    <salute>My dear Charles</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Though dating from Brook S<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>., I am beginning this letter from the house of a patient— Its purport is to thank you for the very interesting volume on the orchids, which you have been good enough to send me;<ref target="#foot.f2"/> the major half of which I have already perused; &amp; the remainder of which I look to with the same expectation of pleasure</p>
<p>There are two or three comments which occur to me on the subject, as it bears upon the principle of “natural selection”. But these matters lie beyond the limits of a note, &amp; I will not enter upon them now. I earnestly wish your time, &amp; your health, gave us more frequent opportunities of meeting &amp; talking over these subjects.</p>
<p>I should gladly hear of any improvement in the state of your little Boy, as respects this singular form of malady.<ref target="#foot.f3"/> Let me know if there is anything which can be considered a change in the character of the symptoms</p>
<p>Ever, my dear Sir | Yours affec<hi rend="superscript">ly</hi> | H Holland</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is provided by reference to the publication of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6010.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Orchids</hi></ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Holland’s name appears on the presentation list CD drew up for <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6010.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Orchids</hi></ref> (see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 10, Appendix IV).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">Holland refers to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1226.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Horace Darwin</ref> (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-3485.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Henry Holland, 26 March [1862]</ref>).</note>
